<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id063e4c4c-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d" identifier="/us/usc/t19/s3913"><num value="3913">§ 3913.</num><heading> Delegation of authorities</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The President may delegate the duties and authorities under this chapter to such officers, officials, departments, or agencies of the United States Government as the President deems appropriate.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id063e4c4d-3a70-11f1-8ace-823fb135378d">(<ref href="/us/pl/108/19/s14">Pub. L. 108–19, § 14</ref>, <date date="2003-04-25">Apr. 25, 2003</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/117/636">117 Stat. 636</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
